text: on Independence Square protesters have
been busy putting up barricades all
around here to stop police getting onto
the square and they've been writing
messages on the barricades this one for
example says Ukraine for freedom here
they've written Ukraine for the EU
that's because the protesters here
believe their future lies with Europe
they're deeply disappointed that their
president president yanukovych refused
to sign the association agreement with
the EU that would have brought Ukraine
closer to Brussels as you can see
they've been collecting anything they
could get their hands on big pieces of
wood metal to use as barricades now a
lot of the protesters here stayed the
night here and they've been lighting
fires to keep themselves warm you can
see a group they're still warming
themselves and they're determined to
stay here on Independence Square until
their demands are met and they are the
resignation of the president and the
Prime Minister well this is the center
of Independence Square as you can see at
the moment I've got a lot of people
milling around here and you see that big
green metal structure over there that
sort of artificial Christmas tree where
the protesters have taken some of the
metal from that to use to build up the
barricades as you can see there's a
stage behind me lots of Ukrainian flags
also flags of the European Union and all
through the night they've been making
political speeches there they've been
singing Ukrainian songs and they've been
demanding political change in Ukraine
